## 3. Error Responses

All errors follow this format:

```json
{
  "detail": "Error message here"
}
```

| Status | Meaning |
|--------|---------|
| 400 | Bad request / validation error |
| 401 | Not authenticated or token expired |
| 403 | Forbidden (not admin) |
| 404 | Resource not found |
| 422 | Request body validation failed |
| 429 | Rate limit exceeded |

For `422`, response includes field-level errors:
```json
{
  "detail": [
    {
      "loc": ["body", "password"],
      "msg": "Password must be at least 8 characters long",
      "type": "value_error"
    }
  ]
}
```

---

## 4. Testing Flow

```
1. GET  /health              -- verify API is running
2. POST /auth/register       -- create test account
3. POST /auth/login          -- get access_token + refresh_token
4. GET  /auth/me             -- verify token works (send Bearer token)
5. POST /search/flights      -- test search (returns mock data)
6. POST /auth/refresh        -- test token refresh before expiry
```

---

## 5. Frontend Integration Notes

- Store [access_token](file:///h:/Trurism/app/core/security.py#68-89) in memory (not localStorage for security)
- Store [refresh_token](file:///h:/Trurism/app/auth/services.py#94-111) in httpOnly cookie or secure storage
- Set `Authorization: Bearer <access_token>` header on all protected requests
- When you get `401`, call `/auth/refresh` with the refresh token
- If refresh also fails, redirect to login
- Access token expires in 15 min, refresh token in 7 days
